<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 11:20PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Ellis
and western Roger Mills Counties through 1145 PM CDT...
At 1119 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a small cluster of strong
thunderstorms from 4 miles southwest of Arnett to Durham and Reydon,
moving northeast at 15 to 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Arnett, Reydon, Crawford, Roll and Durham.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
